1 SENATE FLOOR VERSION
March 2, 2026
2 AS AMENDED
3 SENATE BILL NO. 2049 By: Frix
4
5 An Act relating to transportation; requiring the
Department of Transportation to submit certain
6 notification to the Transportation Commission;
requiring Department to receive certain approval
7 before taking certain action; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
8
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
11 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
12 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1105 of Title 69, unless there
13 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
14 The Department of Transportation shall, prior to making a claim
15 against a surety company for financial loss due to the
16 nonperformance of a contractor engaged in contract with the
17 Department, notify the Transportation Commission of its intent to
18 make such claim. The Transportation Commission shall review the
19 information submitted by the Department and approve or disapprove
20 the making of such claim. The Department shall only proceed with
21 making such claim if the Transportation Commission approves of such.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
23 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON AERONAUTICS AND TRANSPORTATION
March 2, 2026 - DO PASS AS AMENDED
